  "prompt": "Is Masters in Public Health course included in SOL?",
  "response": "Yes, the **Master of Public Health (MPH)** course is included in the **School of Open Learning (SOL)** at the University of Delhi. The program is designed to provide students with knowledge and skills in public health and is offered through the distance education mode. The MPH program at SOL is typically aimed at working professionals and others who wish to pursue higher education in public health but cannot attend regular classes. \n\n### Key Highlights:\n- **Eligibility**: Generally, candidates with a bachelor's degree in any discipline (preferably related to health sciences) are eligible to apply.\n- **Duration**: The course duration is usually 2 years (divided into 4 semesters).\n- **Mode of Study**: Distance learning/online mode.\n- **Curriculum**: Covers topics such as epidemiology, health policy, biostatistics, environmental health, and more.\n\nFor more details, you can visit the official SOL website or contact the admissions office for the latest information on eligibility, application process, and course structure.",
